nodes.text: Jonset was a male Zabrak who lived on Corellia during the Galactic Civil War. By the time following the Battle of Yavin, he would frequent the Coronet City cantina and served as an informant for the Corellian Security Force. Circa 1 ABY, CorSec Lieutenant Mack Jasper sent a spacer to ask Jonset about the Rogue CorSec. Jonset provided information regarding a secret meeting between the Rogue CorSec and the Ragtag gang. Further investigation of the CorSec about the Rogue CorSec/Ragtag connexion would led to the discovery of a plot to overthrow the Diktat Daclif Gallamby himself.

Jonset was a non-player character in the 2003 video game Star Wars Galaxies, a massively multiplayer online role-playing game developed by Sony Online Entertainment and published by LucasArts, prior to its closure on December 15, 2011.

Jonset was added to the game with the expansion Star Wars Galaxies: Trials of Obi-Wan, released on November 1, 2005. He was part of questline that featured the Rogue CorSec plot against the Diktat. This story arc was later slightly revamped with the release of the "Publish 27", on February 15, 2006, as the questline was integrated into the "Legacy Quest", the main questline in the game.
